cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for medical image analysis, specifically for bone age assessment using CT images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of a novel convolutional neural network, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which suggests the category of cs.MED (Medical Imaging). The use of deep learning techniques for age estimation also falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the use of a dataset and comparison with common deep architectures, which suggests the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
